gerechte Wirtschaftsordnung (Christians for a Just Economic Order) promotes the study of land and monetary
reform theories in the light of Jewish, Christian and Islamic religious doctrines critical of land speculation and
the taking of interest. Margrit Kennedy, Helmut Creutz and other authors have examined the contemporary
relevance of Gesell's economic model and tried to bring his ideas up to date."
